description:
Modern European Art
Thames and Hudson Ltd | 1985 | ISBN: 0151610002 | English | 228 pages | PDF | 37.6 MB
With 207 Illustrations

Alan Bowness offers a lucid analysis of art during the last hundred years, showing how experiment and tradition have enriched one another. Beginning with the naturalist tendencies of the Imp! ionists in the 1860s and 1870s, he follows the progression of art towards constantly new methods of expression: Expressionism, Cubism, Constructivism, Surrealism, Abstraction, and so on to the present day
